  "body": "<!-- Please only use this template for submitting enhancement requests -->\r\n\r\n**What would you like to be added**:\r\nActually, the parameter `--prune` depends to all namespaces in the cluster. Filtering is only possible with labels. When running `kubectl --namespace NAMESPACE --prune -f ` the `prune` should only depend on the objects defined in `NAMESPACE`.\r\n\r\n**Why is this needed**:\r\nA typical use-case is having one repository and namespace per project. When working with declarative objects it should be possible to remove objects and get them pruned like having them described in the respository.\r\nThis would also help when renaming objects within the repository - which actually needs a manual `kubectl delete` on the host for the old objects.\r\n\r\nThis even could be a better solution for the problem described in https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/57916",
